  "prompt": "Do some people not have dandruffs?",
  "response": "Yes, some people do not have dandruff. Dandruff is a condition that results from an overproduction of skin cells on the scalp, combined with factors like dryness, fungal infections (Malassezia), and sensitivity to hair care products. However, not everyone is affected by these factors or has the condition. Individual differences like genetics, skin type, and hygiene practices can contribute to whether a person experiences dandruff or not.\n\nMaintaining a clean scalp, using suitable hair products, and addressing any underlying health issues can help prevent dandruff for many people. Moreover, some individuals naturally have balanced sebum production and do not experience the issues that lead to dandruff.",
